abstract: Jason Kilar, who helped build Hulu into a popular online video site, said he would step down, and provided no indication of what he would do next.

lead_paragraph: 8:39 p.m. | Updated Jason Kilar, the Web wizard who turned Hulu from a punch line into a popular source of online video, said on Friday that he would step down as the site’s founding chief executive in the next three months.

lead_paragraph: Let’s start the new year on scientifically sound footing by addressing some nutritional falsehoods that circulate widely in cyberspace, locker rooms, supermarkets and health food stores. As a result, millions of people are squandering hard-earned dollars on questionable, even hazardous foods and supplements.

abstract: Looking ahead to the new year’s offerings in music, theater, film, TV and video games in New York.
snippet: Looking ahead to the new year’s offerings in music, theater, film, TV and video games in New York.
lead_paragraph: THE year may not be over yet, but sometimes it is hard to tamp down the enthusiasm of critics, reporters and editors for what’s aesthetically ahead. In picking their favorite possibilities for 2013, writers for The New York Times have identified a high-octane cast in “Parsifal” at the Metropolitan Opera, a celebration of Cambodian culture, a series of major video game releases and a sizzling dose of televised Bacon, as in the actor Kevin.

abstract: Ranking among the most devastating residential fires in New York City history, the flames that enveloped Breezy Point, Queens, left a hole in the heart of the genial shore community.
snippet: Ranking among the most devastating residential fires in New York City history, the flames that enveloped Breezy Point, Queens, left a hole in the heart of the genial shore community.
lead_paragraph: They expected the sea to come, though not like this. Tim Dufficy, 26, one of the volunteer firefighters, had relocated his two cars to the rooftop lot of a Brooklyn mall so they would be up high. Of potential risks, fire did not rouse much concern. They began the evening contemplating turkey.

abstract: The story of three friends from Galveston, Tex., seems less a tribute to upward mobility than a study of obstacles in an age of economic inequality.
snippet: The story of three friends from Galveston, Tex., seems less a tribute to upward mobility than a study of obstacles in an age of economic inequality.
lead_paragraph: GALVESTON, Tex. — Angelica Gonzales marched through high school in Goth armor — black boots, chains and cargo pants — but undermined her pose of alienation with a place on the honor roll. She nicknamed herself after a metal band and vowed to become the first in her family to earn a college degree.

abstract: If we want to stem violence, we need to begin by stemming despair.
snippet: If we want to stem violence, we need to begin by stemming despair.
lead_paragraph: SUICIDE is not as newsworthy as homicide. A person’s disaffection with his own life is less threatening than his rage to destroy others. So it makes sense that since the carnage in Newtown, Conn., the press has focused on the victims — the heartbreaking, senseless deaths of children, and the terrible pain that their parents and all the rest of us have to bear. Appropriately, we mourn Adam Lanza’s annihilation of others more than his self-annihilation.
